-- Iran Arrests ‘Several’ Spies Seeking to Disrupt Vote, Fars Says
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2012-01-09T08:45:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/iran-arrests-several-spies-seeking-to-disrupt-vote-fars-says.html
Iran  has arrested “several” people
suspected of spying and planning to disrupt parliamentary
elections on March 2, Intelligence Minister Heidar Moslehi said,
according to state-run Fars news agency.  The people were working for the U.S., Moslehi said, Fars
 reported .  To contact the reporter on this story:
